    "urn:li:comment:(activity:7468657199297355777,7468661880673296385)": {
      "comment_urn": "urn:li:comment:(activity:7468657199297355777,7468661880673296385)",
      "commented_at": "2026-06-05T13:55:53Z",
      "verb": "commented",
      "text": "The \"if those assumptions were people, I'd take them to court\" line is exactly how it feels when you reread these things after a few years. 😅\n\nThe one I'm most glad to have dropped sounds embarrassingly close to one of yours: I thought a good leader can put themselves in anyone's shoes if they just try hard enough. Then last year I caught myself quietly judging our founder for caring — intensely — about a dying phone battery, and realized that assumption was running the whole show. The fix wasn't trying harder to understand, it was accepting that I won't. That swap cleaned up something on the leadership side I didn't even know was breaking.",
      "comment_author_name": "Peter Ovchynnikov",
      "comment_author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ovchyn",
      "post_urn": "urn:li:activity:7468661946834268160",
